d 'XTDYNESTIMB': module implementing dynamic linear panel-data estimators robust to structural breaks, long-T overidentification, and error cross-sectional dependence
d
d	 xtdynestimb estimates the dynamic linear panel-data model 
d	y_it = a_1 y_i,t-1 + ... + a_p y_i,t-p + x_it' b + eta_i [+
d f_t] + v_it	 with three modern estimators that each address a
d different failure of the textbook Arellano-Bond /   
d Blundell-Bond GMM estimator:	      o Structural breaks. Mean
d shifts in the fixed effects invalidate the standard difference
d and system		moment conditions. dd adds the break-robust
d double-difference moment conditions of Chowdhury &	       
d Russell (2017) (both the instruments and the equation are in
d differences) and offers five nested		 estimators.	   
d o Error cross-sectional dependence. Common factors make the
d lagged-level instruments invalid. csdgmm	      removes the
d common factors by cross-sectional (time) demeaning and,
d optionally, restricts the	       instrument set to the
d regressors only (Sarafidis 2009).	   o Long-T
d overidentification bias. When T is large the number of AB moment
d conditions grows like T^2,		biasing the estimator. 
d ablasso uses period-by-period LASSO to keep only the most
d informative		 instruments and cross-fitting to remove
d the over-fitting bias (Chernozhukov, Fernandez-Val, Huang &	   
d      Wang 2024). 
d
d KW: dynamic panel data
d KW: DPD
d KW: structural breaks
d KW: cross-sectional dependence
d KW: overidentification biad
d
d Requires: Stata version 16
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260611
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
f xtdynestimb_predict.ado
f xtdynestimb.ado
f xtdynestimb_ablasso.sthlp
f xtdynestimb_csdgmm.sthlp
f xtdynestimb_dd.sthlp
f xtdynestimb_postestimation.sthlp
f xtdynestimb.sthlp
f xtdynestimb_example.do
